Package jetbrains.mps.typechecking

Class TypecheckingFacade

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.typechecking.backend.TypecheckingSessionHandler
      • jetbrains.mps.typechecking.TypecheckingFacade
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TypecheckingComputations, TypecheckingQueries
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TypecheckingFacadeComponent.ContextTypecheckingFacade
    public abstract class TypecheckingFacade
extends TypecheckingSessionHandler
implements TypecheckingQueries, TypecheckingComputations
    The fa√ßade to launching typechecking operations. This is the entry point for executing typechecking queries, requesting new sessions, and running special computations either in "isolation" or reusing a shared session.

    This class is a mixin of TypecheckingSessionHandler and TypecheckingQueries and provides the implementation for the latter, which uses the backend API for selecting the correct provider and then forwards the query to it.

    One should not try to cache instances of this class, rather the method getFromContext() should be used exclusively, and the instance management is up to the implementation.

      • getFromContext

        @NotNull
public static TypecheckingFacade getFromContext()
        Provides access to an instance of TypecheckingFacade that is available from the environment. The implementation is responsible for selecting the correct facade instance depending on the context, such as whether the current thread is a UI thread etc.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if no instance is available in the current context.

      • coerceType

        public SNode coerceType​(SNode type,
                        @NotNull
                        SConcept typeConcept)
        Description copied from interface: TypecheckingQueries
        Tries to coerce a type to the form represented with the specified typeConcept. More specifically, the most generic instance of a target type that can be represented with targetConcept is constructed. Then the specified type is converted to that target type, which serves as a pattern. If conversion is possible, the result of the conversion is the coerced type. Returns the coerced type or null, if the type can't be coerced to the specified form. To support the legacy contract, nullable type parameter is accepted, in which case null is returned.
        Specified by:
        coerceType in interface TypecheckingQueries

      • coerceType

        @Nullable
public SNode coerceType​(SNode type,
                        @NotNull
                        INodeMatchingPattern targetPattern)
        Description copied from interface: TypecheckingQueries
        Tries to coerce a type to the form corresponding to the specified targetPattern. This is a more specific variant of the method TypecheckingQueries.coerceType(SNode, SConcept), with the difference being that in addition to the target concept one can specify one or more features of the target type. Returns the coerced type or null, if the type can't be coerced to the specified form. To support the legacy contract, nullable type parameter is accepted, in which case null is returned.
        Specified by:
        coerceType in interface TypecheckingQueries

      • checkRecursively

        public void checkRecursively​(SNode root,
                             Consumer<? super NodeReportItem> errorsConsumer)
        Description copied from interface: TypecheckingQueries
        Runs typechecking on a node and all its children recursively, collecting the errors reported. The implementation may employ different strategies when deciding whether to run type checking every time or use cached info. Regardless of whether types were checked or not, the {@param errorsConsumer} must receive all errors reported as if root was really checked.
        Specified by:
        checkRecursively in interface TypecheckingQueries
